GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Man, it's good to be bad sometimes.
~z~Yes, I don't want anyone to get burnt - how about a kiss?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~是的，我也不想有人受伤，来个吻怎么样？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I always think that place is full of crooks - what do you like about it?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我一直觉得那里罪犯很多，你觉得呢？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Here again Niko? Let's go for a stroll.
~z~I don't think you can afford me just yet, Niko.
~z~The food was too good - I can't believe I ate all that.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这里的吃的真好吃，我竟然吃了这么多。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~That was really odd - and that place was full of crooks.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~那可真是奇怪，而且那里罪犯很多。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~A tie is the best result, really.
~z~Niko are you aware of the consequences of that kind of thing? People get hurt, end up in court, you know.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~Niko，你知道这种事的后果吗？会有人受伤，最后会上法庭的。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I really don't know about that sort of thing, Michelle.
~z~That place is crawling with gangsters - what's the appeal to you?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~那家店到处都是黑帮，你怎么想的？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Fun place, but I think it was full of gangsters!
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~有趣的地方，但我觉得那里到处都是黑帮！

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Sure, I like you, but let's be careful. Make sure no one gets burnt.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~当然，我喜欢你。但我们要小心，确保没有人受伤。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I'm new here. It's the only place I know, really.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我是新来的。我只知道这家店，真的。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~You think I'm a whore, is that it? I bet this'll end up on the internet. Fuck you.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你把我当成妓女，是这样吗？我会把这事发到网上的。操你妈。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I hope I don't have my cholesterol checked any time soon.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~希望我不会很快去检查胆固醇。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~That was fun, but to me those girls looked like they were on drugs.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~很有意思。但我觉得那些女孩可能吸毒了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~No problem - I respect you - maybe we can kiss?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~没问题，我尊重你，那我们亲一个吧？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Oh, Niko, this is our special place, let's go for a walk...
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~噢，Niko，这是我们的二人世界，我们去散步吧...

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~That was great Niko but I think I'm all worn out.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~今天很开心，Niko。但是我已经精疲力尽了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~No problem - I understand. I respect you. How about a kiss?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~没问题，我明白的。我尊重你。亲一个怎么样？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Thanks Niko - that was a lot of fun.
~z~Maybe. It's not my area of expertise.
~z~After today, sure, but if this ends up on the internet, I'll kill you.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~既然约过会了，可以。要是被人传到网上，我杀了你。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Hey, Niko, let's find something else to do, we can't go back yet!
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，Niko，我们再找点事做吧，现在回去太早了！

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Okay, no problem - how about a kiss?
~z~Great, but I hope you don't kiss and tell.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~好啊，但希望你不要拿这事到处吹嘘。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I guess we're both tourists in this city, aren't we?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我们大概都是这个城市的游客吧？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Are you gonna take me back or what?
~z~I'd love to finish pool one time.
~z~I think we should stay out and have some more fun - you got any ideas?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我觉得我们应该多在外面玩一会儿，你有想法吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~It's really good to experience Liberty City with someone else who isn't from here.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~和没来过自由城的人一起玩真是太棒了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Why do we go to Comrades so often - seems full of criminals to me?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~为什么你总来Comrades？这里似乎到处都是罪犯。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~We left too early - I was sort of enjoying that in a weird way.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我们走得太早了，我在一定程度上看得还挺高兴。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~It's been interesting I guess, time to call it a night though.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~今天很有趣，不过这次就先这样吧。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~A tie is the most fun - let's play pool again soon.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~平局最有趣了。下次再来打桌球吧。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Oh, you wanna go for a walk here again? Niko, you old romantic.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~噢，你又想去那里散步？Niko，老派的浪漫。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Irish mobsters? I'd have no idea about that.
~z~Most American guys race a girl back to her place at the end of a date - what gives, Niko?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~大多数美国男人约完会都会送女孩回家，这是为什么，Niko？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Is that all I am, a cheap fuck?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这就是我的价值吗？把我当鸡？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Next time, can we finish a game?
~z~Hey, you beat me. Now you've got to tell me a secret about yourself.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，你打败我了。现在你得告诉我一个关于你自己的小秘密。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Why do you like that place so much?
~z~I can't believe they call this shit entertainment.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~他们居然管这种东西叫娱乐。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~This is a great idea, Niko, I love seeing a bit of the city, we should go for a walk...
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这真是个好主意，Niko。我很乐意看看这个城市，我们应该去散散步...

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~This really is a beautiful city, isn't it? Sometimes you can just forget about all the crime and stuff here, can't you?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这座城市真美啊，不是吗？在这里时甚至可以把一切罪过都忘掉，不是吗?

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Niko, you remembered, this is our place!
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~Niko, 你记住，这是我们的二人世界！

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~God, Niko, I'm exhausted, you've tired me out.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~天哪，Niko，我累坏了，你可把我累坏了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Hey, I won. As a reward can you tell me some stuff about what you did before you got here?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，我赢了。作为奖励，你能告诉我你来自由城之前的事吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Oh my God - I can't believe this!
~z~You seem to like going to Perestroika. Why is that?
~z~Can I come up for a nice hot coffee?
~z~Well, it's been fun, but I can't stay out any longer.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~玩得很高兴，但我不能再待在外面了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Next time, we should play a proper game and finish it.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~下次，我们应该从头到尾完整比完。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I'm really enjoying myself Niko, but I'm real tired.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我真的很高兴，Niko，但我真的累了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~No you can't, I don't know you that well.
~z~Okay, you beat me at bowling. Now the least you can do is open up to me a little.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~好吧，你打保龄球赢了我。那现在你至少对我敞开一点心扉吧。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~It's amazing that this city can be so pretty but so dangerous too, don't you think?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这个城市如此美丽，但也如此危险，不是很奇妙吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~You really like that place, don't you?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你真的很喜欢那个地方，不是吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Can you drop me back at my place?
~z~I'm getting a little antsy Niko, I hope we're gonna be there soon?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我有一点烦了，Niko。我们过多久能到啊？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~This is funny - just not as they intended.
~z~Liberty City is an amazing place, isn't it? That's probably why it attracts so many crooks, don't you think, Niko?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~自由城是个神奇的地方，不是吗？可能因此才会引来这么多罪犯吧，你不这么想吗，Niko？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Why'd you quit bowling, Niko? It's almost like you don't want me to find out about your life.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~Niko，你怎么不打了？好像你不想让我了解你的生活一样。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Weird crowd in that place - packed with criminals.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~那家店的顾客很怪，都是罪犯。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~This is a great spot, Niko, I can't remember when I last came here. Why don't we have a look around?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这真是个好地方，Niko。我都不记得上次来是什么时候了。要么我们四处转转吧？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Jeez Niko, you sure do pick your date locations, this is a long trip.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~天哪，Niko，你真会挑约会地点，这次路好远。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Most of the time, I'm kind of depressed, but there are moments when I'm happy to be in Liberty City.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~大多数时候我都有点沮丧，但也有一些时候，我很高兴能来自由城。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I've never been there before. But I think some of the guys in there might have been gangsters.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我从未去过那里，但里面好像有黑帮的人。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Well, now that you've lost to me at bowling you've got nothing to hide from me.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~嗯，既然你在保龄球比赛中输给了我，你就不能对我隐瞒了。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Okay, I guess you've got something important to do. What is it?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~好吧，我猜你有重要的事要做。什么事？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Hey, we tied. I like you, Niko. I'd like you even more if you were more honest about what you do for a living.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~嘿，我们平了。我喜欢你，Niko。如果你能告诉我更多关于你工作的事，我会更喜欢你。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Are you gonna escort me to my apartment?
~z~Are we gonna do something or what Niko?
~z~You seem to like hanging out in Irish bars. Why?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你好像很喜欢爱尔兰酒吧。为什么？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Hmm, this sure is a long trip...
~z~Why don't you give me a lift home?
~z~It's been okay, Niko, but I'm beat.
~z~Don't you think this is funny, Niko?
~z~I'm beat Niko, I guess having fun does that to you.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我好累啊，Niko，我猜这是快乐的副作用。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Interesting bar - do you think those guys were crooks?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~有趣的酒吧，你觉得那些人是罪犯吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~What is it with you and the Irish?
~z~I don't know. It's the Eastern Bloc thing, I suppose.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我不知道。大概是东欧圈的缘故吧。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I don't think I'm ready to go home yet, you wanna do something else?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我还没打算回家，你想再做点别的吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I'd invite you in for some coffee, but it'd cost at least, say... $20m
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我很乐意请你喝杯咖啡，但怎么说也要...两千万美元吧。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I need to get back to my place, will you take me?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~我需要回家了，你能带我去吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~It just reminds me of home, I guess.
~z~That was naughty - I can't believe we ate all that crap!
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~太可怕了，没想到我们把那玩意吃完了！

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I told you I was good at darts, Niko.
~z~Irish mobsters? I have no idea about that.
~z~What do you like about those Irish places?
~z~Are you going to invite me in? For a coffee, I mean?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你会请我进去吗？就是进去喝杯咖啡？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~What a strange crowd - they all belonged in jail.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~这些顾客好怪，他们应该在坐牢的。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~We should have stayed to the end.
~z~I told you I was great at pool.
~z~Why did you stop? We weren't finished yet.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你怎么不玩了？还没分出胜负呢。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Umm, I don't know about that kind of thing.
~z~For coffee or something? I don't want to get burned Niko.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~真的是喝咖啡吗？我不想被骗，Niko。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I think I'm funnier than that guy.
~z~You going to invite me upstairs, for coffee or something?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~你要请我上楼喝杯咖啡什么的吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~She's a nice girl, but there's something weird about her.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~她人确实挺好，但就是有一些古怪。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Interesting place - seems like the kind of place Irish mobsters would like to hang out, don't you think?
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~有趣的地方。似乎是爱尔兰黑帮喜欢去的地方，你不觉得吗？

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~Uh, it's just the first place I went to.
GCM3AUD.translated: ~z~呃，因为这是我最早去的一家店。

GCM3AUD.original: ~z~I don't know about that kind of thing.
~z~That was fun, is there something else you want to do?
